<br>
Me name be Hakthin Redsteel, but me friends call me Hak n' Slash.  I have been readin' yer information fer many days, and found it to be most interestin'.  All o' it has helped me a bunch.  Me highest lvl character is a 43rd season High Elf Magician, but to be honest wit ya, he gets ta be a bit borin'.  I have decided to play a warrior, and Im up ta me 15th season and climbing hopin' ta be in me 40s in a month or two.  Me question is a simple one fer all o' yas methinks, so here goes.<br>
<br>
I am a dwarf btw, if that helps anything.  And no, I aint makin' no stinkin' ogre.  (no offense to the ogres, there is just enuff o ya).  I have been keepin' up me weapon skills, all me 1 handed skills are maxed out and working on my 2h slash with an axe o the iron back.  Gonna save up and buy a mithril staff by the time I am 20 I hope, and will start 2h blunt at that time.  But, me question is 'bout duel wielding.<br>
<br>
I have heard that you should go fer speed in yer primary hand and ration in the second.  I have a crystal fiber (8/26), a yak, a dragoon dirk(just ta keep up piercing) and a bullsmasher(6/20 NOT magic.)<br>
<br>
Which weapon would you put in yer primary in which in your secondary hand?  Yer help would be most apprecated.<br>
<br>
Thank ye once again and ahead o' time.<br>
Hakthin Redsteel <p>Mikhal Goldrealm...Magician of the 40th Conjuration</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unailened.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nailened</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/6/01 1:22:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question for the High and Mighty!</span><hr size=1> Well.  First off I want to say that DWARF WARRIORS RULE!!!  Now on to your questions.  This is a fairly contraversial topic.  I always have used and most likely will use my weapons with faster weapon (lower delay) in pri with off hand being a harder hitting weapon.  Now that also is dependant on weapon availablity and procs.  Looking at your weapon choices , your level only one thing bothers me.  The bullsmasher unfortunately is not a magic weapon.  Now, if you find yourself having to kill ghouls or etc. you're gonna need a magic weapon.  I would do this:<br>
<br>
Pri - Yak<br>
Off - Fiber<br>
<br>
Now, the yak won't proc at your level but that's no biggie.  This gives you the better damage (8 vs. 6) and still keeps both weapons at a fairly low delay. I would try to get a faster weapon (DWARVEN SAP) to replace that fiber and smasher.  Then the sap would go primary and yak in off hand.  The dwarven sap is a very nice weapon that you can take advantage of since you are a dwarf.  The delay of 20 on it will help taunt alot and the yak with a delay of 24 would put both of your weapons under a delay of 25 and still allow you to keep all weapon skills up (just switch out pri with piercer to work skill).  Just my 2cp worth.  Hope it helps!<br>
<br>
Lomax Loatheheart<br>
54th Dwarven Champion<br>
Hope's Beginning<br>
Vazaelle<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umikhalgoldrealm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikhal Goldrealm</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/6/01 1:35:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question for the High and Mighty!</span><hr size=1> Thank ye fer yer advice me friend.  Only problem is that I only gots 100pp to me name right now, and no 2handed blunt.  And me normal party requries me to dish out some dmg even when practicin', so I figured I needed the mithril staff for 2h blunt afore I buy me another slasher.  I could use the bull smasher in me main hand fer now, and switch it around against them critters that need magic weapons.  After the staff, I'll save to buy me a dwarven sap.  Figured it would cost 'round 500pp &lt;shrug&gt; what the equip pages say neways.<br>
<br>
Thank ye once more, keep the info comin'!<br>
Hakthin Redsteel<br>
Dwarven orc basher <p>Mikhal Goldrealm...Magician of the 40th Conjuration</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umezlothemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezlo the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/6/01 2:56:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question for the High and Mighty!</span><hr size=1> The reason they say go with the fastest weapon in your main hand is because your main hand gets a damage bonus.  That means every successfull hit get your whatever you would normally get (2 * weapon damage) + the damage bonus.  This bonus really starts to add up when you are a high level warrior with a fast weapon.<br>
<br>
But at level 20, your damage bonus is 0.  Damage bonus is (level - 25)/3 rounded down.  So at 28th level you get 1 point added to every successful hit.<br>
<br>
Therefor you should go with the best ratio in both hands until that damage bonus starts to get up there.<br>
<br>
p.s. a magician gets a big jump in power at 44th level with shock of steel and an amazing jump at 49th with those awesome 49th level pets <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Keep plugging away at that magicain.  43rd is a painful level.<br>
<br>
 <p>Mezlo, Mage of 52 Seasons, Drinal</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umezlothemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mezlo the Mage</A> at: 6/6/01 3:15:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukazarksnaketongue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazark Snaketongue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/7/01 6:41:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question for the High and Mighty!</span><hr size=1> You use fast weapon in main hand to taunt also.   Main hand swings more then the offhand because offhand is a proc from Duel Wield skill.  Main hand uses delay of weapon and any haste you have.  More swings you get off a mob, the more it gets mad at you even if you miss.  Also main hand gets the damage bonus and if you crit alot it starts adding up.  Use best ratio on off hand for damage purposes.<br>
<br>
Kazark Snaketongue, 60 Iksar Warlord<br>
