<br>
Ebon Razor and a Dwarven Sap off the top of my head are really nice weapons. keep an eye out if you see them. usually sell pretty cheap due to the restriction of classes that can use it.<br>
<br>
primary hand = fastest weapon. for damage and taunt reasons.<br>
off hand = best ratio. make the most of using the dual wield skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukhaladenhowlingwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khaladen Howlingwind</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/7/01 9:06:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://plaza.powersurfr.com/blarg/ralyeon.gif   height=250 width=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question for the High and Mighty!</span><hr size=1> very cheap 2HB to start with - Bloodforge Hammer.  You can quest for it, and it isn't too bad and I believe it is magic. <p><center><font size=5><font face="comic sans ms" color=blue><i><b>Ralyeon Steelheart</b></i><br>
